name: protein-glutamine glutaminase
classes: Acting on carbon-nitrogen bonds, other than peptide bonds;
reaction: protein L-glutamine + H2O = protein L-glutamate + NH3 [RN:R02622]
comment: Specific for the hydrolysis of the gamma-amide of glutamine substituted at the carboxyl position or both the alpha-amino and carboxyl positions, e.g., L-glutaminylglycine and L-phenylalanyl-L-glutaminylglycine.

orthologs.K03412: two-component system, chemotaxis family, protein-glutamate methylesterase/glutaminase

references.title: Peptidoglutaminase. Enzymes for selective deamidation of gamma-amide of peptide-bound glutamine.
